race.comment: BAVETTE (3) is the most lightly-raced horse in the field, but the plus there is that he looks to have more upside than any of his rivals. Brings winning form into this off a nice effort at Swan Hill, when well back, and the way he went about his business that day suggested the extra trip here will be no issue at all. YAM (2) hit a purple patch of form last preparation and while he hasn't been able to rediscover that this preparation, he has been up in grade and might be finally ready to show his best with the benefit of three runs back. AIMING (6) resumes and while she generally improves with a run under the belts, she did enough at the jumpouts to suggest she can play a role here. SAVAMOON (8) ended last campaign as a winner and could return the same way.
